\pard\f0\fs28  {\b 9. T. parnassi} Boiss. & Spruner in Boiss., {\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1} ({\b 2}): 30 (1843). Suffruticose perennial, glabrous, caespitose, stems 1-3 cm. Leaflets 3-6 mm, obovate or obcordate. Stipules ovate, acuminate. Heads up to 12-flowered, not paired; peduncles 10-30 mm, equalling or longer than the leaves. Bracts longer than the pedicels. Calyx glabrous; teeth ovate-triangular, imbricate, ½ as long as the tube. Corolla 5-8 mm, pink. •{\i   Mountains of Greece.} Gr.
