\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b orbelicum} (Velen.) Pawl., {\i  Zapiski Fl. Tatr}{\b  4}: 9 (1949): Stems often short, but sometimes elongate and rooting at the nodes. Leaflets 6-8 mm, obovate-cuneate. Heads dense; peduncles up to 120 mm. Calyx-tube 6- to 8-veined with only 6 veins distinct; upper calyx-teeth 1½ times as long as the tube; corolla 8-10 mm, cream; standard 2-2½ times as long as the calyx. •{\i   Carpathians and mountains of Balkan peninsula}.
